post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text:
Re-Enrollment

Dear Regent Park Scholars Academy Parent,

It is time to re-enroll your child at Regent Park for next school year. We realize we asked you for this information already. However, we do another survey just in case your circumstances have changed. This confirmation ensures your child has a seat in our school for the upcoming year.

You can re-enroll your child through the online Parent Portal. Log in at
Regentparkscholars.org. The login is located at the top right corner of the webpage. If you do not have a Parent Portal account, create one by calling 866-642-3676 and a parent relations representative will assist you. Once you’re logged in, you can complete the survey and update your contact information.

For questions, or to complete your re-enrollment survey, and update your contact information over the phone, please call the school office at 313-371-1300. We look forward to continuing to have your family as members of our school community.

Sincerely,

C.Byse
Principal

post_text:
Hello,

Gleaners Distribution will take place Friday, January 11th in the school parking lot from 1:30 p.m. - until......First, come/first serve

Your menu for Friday is listed below:

· Milk & Eggs- based upon household size

· Toasty O’s Cereal

· Yellow Split Peas

· Frozen Carrots

· Winter Squash

· Blueberries

· Strawberry Fruit Cups- 8 per family

*Families will receive one of everything.
